111.subject: SOMS
111.courseDescription: Principles of Academic and Personal Development. Credit 0 to 1. Identification of personal goals and learning skills promoting academic and career success; development of personal leadership strengths, styles, motivation and values; personal development planning for self-improvement. Prerequisite: Freshman classification or approval of instructor.

180.subject: SOMS
180.courseDescription: Survey of Performance Based Training Methods. (1-0). Credit 1. Introduction to performance oriented training methods and techniques; key concepts and generalizations of training and identification of training needs; study of representative theories of workplace training, performance evaluation, and experiential training techniques. Prerequisite: Freshman classification or approval of instructor.

181.subject: SOMS
181.courseDescription: Developing and Instructing Others. Credit 0. Introduction to leadership, mentoring and instructing others in the specific context of military-style training; survey of basic military performance counseling skills; introduction to subordinate instruction and evaluation techniques. Prerequisites: Freshman classification or approval of instructor.

280.subject: SOMS
280.courseDescription: Fundamentals of Peer Leadership. (1-0). Credit 1. Introduction to theories of peer leadership when applied to a specific context; fundamentals and techniques of small group communication; performance evaluation; survey of basic supervisory skills. Prerequisite: Sophomore classification or approval of instructor.

281.subject: SOMS
281.courseDescription: Fundamentals of Intentional Leadership. Credit 0 to 1.  Exposure to the fundamentals of intentional leadership, deliberate practice, planning and leadership assessment; development of initial personal leadership development plans; alignment of personal and organizational values, vision, mission, purpose and goals toward desired outcomes. Prerequisites: Grade of C or better in SOMS 280 or approval of department head or director.

289.subject: SOMS
289.courseDescription: Special Topics in...  Credit 1 to 4. Selected topics in an identified area of leadership theory and practice. May be repeated for credit. Prerequisites: Freshman or sophomore classification; approval of instructor.

380.subject: SOMS
380.courseDescription: Workshop in Leadership Education. Credit 0 to 1. The study of leadership theory, intra group relationships, assessment tools for skills development, and techniques for achieving group goals. Prerequisite: Junior classification or approval of instructor.

381.subject: SOMS
381.courseDescription: Workshop in Leadership Education II. Credit 0 to 1. Continuation of SOMS 380. Fundamentals of small group dynamics; interpersonal communication; application of selected leadership theories; interpretation of individual assessments to include personality traits, values, and signature strengths. Prerequisites: SOMS 380; junior or senior classification.

481.subject: SOMS
481.courseDescription: Seminar in Executive Leadership. Credit 0 to 1. The study of contemporary leadership issues, organizational effectiveness, problem solving, and decision making. Prerequisite: Senior classification or approval of instructor.

482.subject: SOMS
482.courseDescription: Seminar in Executive Leadership II. Credit 0 to 1. Continuation of SOMS 481. Discussion of ethical dilemmas in leadership roles; ethical decision-making; personal accountability in organizational settings. Prerequisite: SOMS 481 or approval of instructor.

485.subject: SOMS
485.courseDescription: Directed Studies.  Credit 1 to 4. Individual supervision of special readings or assigned projects to promote independent study; program enrichment for capable students; written and oral reports required. Prerequisite: Approval of instructor.

489.subject: SOMS
489.courseDescription: Special Topics in...  Credit 1 to 4. Selected topics in an identified area of leadership theory and practice. May be repeated for credit. Prerequisites: Junior or senior classification; approval of instructor.
